// @check
// @error not all code paths return a value in 'f'
// CONTRACT (must-error): a NON-void function whose body can fall off the end without
// yielding a value on some path traps at runtime (the wasm result-type fallthrough), so
// the checker must reject it. Here `n <= 0` falls through with no return. Distinct from
// the exhaustive-`is`/literal-chain rule (those are adjudicated by the dedicated
// exhaustiveness check) — this is the GENERAL totality rule over a plain `if` guard.
function f(n: i32): i32 {
  if n > 0 { return 1 }
}
print(f(1))
